Adult.description: Orange-crowned Warblers are greener and less brown than female Black-throated Blue Warblers. Orange-crowned's undertail coverts are yellow (not white). Note thin bill and lack of white square on the wing.

Nonbreeding/immature.description: Nonbreeding/immature Tennessee Warblers have yellow-washed throat and flanks, while female Black-throated Blues are more dusky and brownish. Tennessee also lacks the female Black-throated Blue's white square on the wing.

Female.description: Female American Redstarts have yellow flashes in the wings and tail that Black-throated Blue Warblers do not have.

Adult female.description: Female Pine Warblers have 2 white wingbars while female Black-throated Blue Warblers have a white square on the wing.

Female.description: Female Common Yellowthroats have a yellow throat and undertail coverts while female Black-throated Blue Warblers have a dusky throat and white undertail coverts. Note lack of white square on the wing.
